{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "One of the most commonly utilized emergent abilities in commonsense reasoning tasks is \"in-context learning\" [51].",
    "This refers to the model's ability to understand and adapt to new information or tasks based on the context provided in the conversation or text.",
    "It enables effective reasoning without the need for explicit programming or additional data training, thereby allowing it to generate the required content based on the provided input text or sequence without the need for further model parameter updates.",
    "Our method builds on LLMs, but it is model-agnostic and can be adapted to any LLM to improve their commonsense explanation generation ability.Commonsense knowledge is often captured by LLMs because these models learn from large amounts of text data, which implicitly contain patterns that represent how people think and act in everyday situations.",
    "Even though commonsense knowledge is rarely stated explicitly in the text, it is often embedded in the context, relationships and frequent associations between words, phrases and concepts."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "One of the most commonly utilized emergent abilities in commonsense reasoning tasks is \"in-context learning\" [51]."
  ]
}